# tkv2 - loading/empty/error state helper

Slice `tkv2-tri-state`: `std.ui.state` provides a pure `.ssc` helper for
fetched views that already track loading, empty, and error signals.

[signal](std/ui/primitives.ssc)
[loadState, stateName, errorText, triStateText](std/ui/state.ssc)
[lower](std/ui/lower.ssc)
[defaultTheme](std/ui/theme.ssc)
[text](std/ui/typography.ssc)

```scalascript
val loading = signal("triLoading", true)
val empty   = signal("triEmpty", true)
val error   = signal("triError", "network")
val state   = loadState(loading, empty, error)
val name    = stateName(state)

// Priority: loading > error > empty > ready.
println(name())
loading.set(false)
println(name())
error.set("")
println(name())
empty.set(false)
println(name())

val msg = errorText(state, "error:")
println(msg())
error.set("offline")
println(msg())

val tree = triStateText(state, text("ready"), "loading", "empty", "error:")
val view = lower(tree, defaultTheme)
println("tri-state-built")
```
